Fourteen clubs have confirmed participation at the Embu Sevens slated for May 7 -8 at the Njukuri Showground, Embu County. The tournament returns after a two-year hiatus due to the Covid -19 pandemic. Kenya Cup and Championship clubs are among those heading east of the capital, where they will be using the event as preparations for the start of the national Sevens circuit on May 21, with Kabeberi Sevens at the RFUEA ground. Among the teams expected are KCB, Menengai Oilers, Nakuru, British Army, Nondescripts, Mean Machine, Masinde Muliro University of Science and Technology (MMUST), Catholic Monks, Mwamba and USIU Martials. Blak Blad, Meru RFC, Kiambu RFC, Rongai Morans are also expected. Embu Rugby chairman Moses Mukabane expects more teams to register in the course of the week. "We expect more teams to attend with the Sevens circuit around the corner. It will be good preparation for the clubs and will help in whipping them into a competitive state by the circuit starts,‚Äù said Mukabane. The former Mean machine player expects a competitive tournament. "It will be a very good event. We do have some of the top teams in the country coming and I believe the players will put in a good show for the fans," said Mukabane, adding that the draw for the tournament will be done in the course of the week. Oilers won the previous edition, beating cross-town rivals Nakuru 14-12 in the Cup final.